  "event_name": "Ft Lewis Mar 18 '79",
  "venue_name": "Fort Lewis - Area CTA-A",
  "event_notes": "10am meet at Fort Lewis (new area for club). Meet at Historic Gate (just inside main gate; Exit 120 off I-5) at 9:30am then drive ~10 miles to the site; $1 fee. No restrooms or water. Optional group departure: meet at NE corner of Southcenter parking lot (Seafirst Bank) at 8:30am.\n\nMar/Apr 1979 recap: new Ft. Lewis area near Steilacoom; described as the most successful meet in club history. Nearly 30 orienteers (including children) finished either the 3.9 km / 9 control novice course or the 5.1 km / 10 control red (intermediate) course. Weather was beautiful; challenging courses; socializing was fun.",
